## Responsiveness

### Breakpoints
```css
/* Mobile-first base styles (< 640px) */

@media (min-width: 640px) {
  /* Tablet */
}

@media (min-width: 1024px) {
  /* Desktop */
}

@media (min-width: 1280px) {
  /* Large desktop */
}
```

### Mobile Priority
- **Navigation:** Simple top nav (no hamburger unless >5 links)
- **Hero constellation:** Scales down, planets stack vertically on mobile
- **Cards:** Single column on mobile, grid on tablet+
- **Typography:** Use `clamp()` for fluid sizing

---

## Accessibility

### Must-Have
- **Semantic HTML** (`<header>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<footer>`)
- **Alt text** for all images/icons
- **ARIA labels** for interactive elements (buttons, links)
- **Keyboard navigation** (tab order makes sense)
- **Focus states** (visible outline on `:focus`)
- **Contrast ratio** WCAG AA minimum (4.5:1 for text)

### Testing
- Test with keyboard only (no mouse)
- Test with screen reader (if possible)
- Test in high contrast mode

